452
00:43:48,884 --> 00:43:54,266
[SPEAKER_08]: So I've lived in Medford for 19 years.

453
00:43:54,326 --> 00:43:56,227
[SPEAKER_08]: The longest I've ever lived anywhere in my life.

454
00:43:56,287 --> 00:43:57,427
[SPEAKER_08]: I've lived all over the country.

455
00:43:58,527 --> 00:44:07,170
[SPEAKER_08]: I have a direct experience with a family member who lives in Medford, who has a condition that makes me really look at Medford

456
00:44:07,774 --> 00:44:09,295
[SPEAKER_08]: and through different lenses.

457
00:44:10,456 --> 00:44:23,323
[SPEAKER_08]: I also retired a few years ago from teaching in the Newton Public Schools, special education, kids all over the board, autism and everything.

458
00:44:23,963 --> 00:44:32,788
[SPEAKER_08]: And I guess I'm really looking at what I can give to Medford and that

459
00:44:36,759 --> 00:45:05,264
[SPEAKER_08]: When I walk and I bike and I run in Medford, and especially if I'm with the person with a condition, I'm really aware of, as you said, at events that they have, at parks like Duggar and Victory that are very hard to access if you're, anyway, physically disabled, sidewalks that aren't okay for wheelchairs, and

460
00:45:07,088 --> 00:45:09,449
